Day 14 – CSS Fonts and Text

CSS lets you style text for better readability and presentation.
Properties:

font-family → changes font style.

font-size → sets text size.

font-weight → makes text bold.

font-style → italicizes text.

text-align → aligns text (left, center, right, justify).

text-decoration → underline, overline, or line-through.

text-transform → uppercase, lowercase, capitalize.
Example:

h1 {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 24px;
  font-weight: bold;
  text-align: center;
}


Using fonts and text styling improves readability and page design.
